# Copy this file to  analyst/.env  and fill in your values.
# .env is git-ignored; this .example is committed as documentation.
# Loaded automatically at startup by dashboard/net.py (load_dotenv).

# ── LLM (board scan) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required for the LLM macro/news board scan. Any OpenAI-compatible endpoint.
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# optional — model name (default: gpt-4o-mini)
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# optional — point at a compatible endpoint (e.g. a proxy/aggregator).
# NOTE: free tiers often cap input tokens (~4096); board_scan.MAX_INSTRUMENTS
# keeps the prompt small to fit.
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1

# ── MetaTrader 5 (demo execution + link monitor) ─────────────────────────────
# ALL OPTIONAL. If omitted, the app attaches to the already-running, logged-in
# MT5 terminal (read-only data + demo trading still work via that session).
#
# Set MT5_LOGIN + MT5_PASSWORD to enable:
#   • the link monitor's auto-reroll to the lowest-ping access point, and
#   • the server-ping CLI:  uv run python -m dashboard.mt5_client --ping <SERVER> [--select]
# These need a login because re-connecting to a server requires credentials.
# Use your DEMO account — the executor refuses to trade a non-demo account.
# MT5_LOGIN=12345678
# MT5_PASSWORD=your-demo-password
# MT5_SERVER=ICMarketsSC-Demo
# MT5_PATH=C:\Program Files\MetaTrader 5\terminal64.exe

# ── News (optional) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Finnhub headlines for the board scan. Falls back to free RSS if unset.
# FINNHUB_API_KEY=...
